Given Scenario: You are hired as a Blue Team member for a company. You are assigned to perform threat intelligence for the company. 
See how you can operationalize the MITRE ATT&CK framework to solve these scenario-based problems.

Your company heavily relies on cloud services like Azure AD, and Office 365 publicly. 
Q: What technique should you focus on mitigating, to prevent an attacker performing Discovery activities if they have obtained valid credentials? (Hint: Not using an API to interact with the cloud environment!) 

A: T1538 Cloud Service Dashboard
https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1538/

Q: You were analyzing a log and found uncommon data flow on port 4050. What APT group might this be? 

A: APT-C-36
https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1571/


Q: The framework has a list of 9 techniques that falls under the tactic to try to get into your network. What is the tactic ID? 

A: TA001 Initial Access
https://attack.mitre.org/tactics/TA0001/ - adversary is trying to access the network

Q: A software prohibits users from accessing their account by deleting, locking the user account, changing password etc. What such software has been documented by the framework?

A: S0372 - Locker Goga
https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1531/

Q: Using ‘Pass the Hash’ technique to enter and control remote systems on a network is common. How would you detect it in your company?

A: Monitor newly created logons and credentials used in events and review for discrepancies.
  https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1550/002/
  Pass the Hash in Mitre Attack - Detection DS0028 Logon Session Creation	
